<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06284078 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06284078 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  STOCK; INVESTMENT; COMPANY; GOVERNMENT; REGULATION; ORGANIZATION; PROBE;FLORIDA; INSURANCE; FINANCE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The Securities and Exchange Commission is investigating whether Merrill Lynchandamp; Co. engaged in trades that helped a Florida insurance company disguise itsdeteriorating financial condition for years, government officials saidWednesday.;   The Merrill inquiry is part of a broader investigation of theactivities of the insurer's parent, Transmark USA Inc.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MERRILL LYNCH UNDER SEC PROBETIES TO AILING INSURER QUESTIONED  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The SEC is examining trades from 1984 to 1988 between Merrill and GuaranteeSecurity Life Insurance Co., Transmark's Jacksonville, Fla.-based insurancesubsidiary.;   The insurer was seized by Florida state insurance regulators inAugust as a result of the collapse in value of its huge junk bond investmentsand what regulators contend was a depletion of its assets by Transmarkofficials.;   In the transactions with Merrill, hundreds of millions ofdollars of government securities were sold by the firm to Guarantee Securityat the end of each year. Almost simultaneously, the firm bought an equaldollar amount of junk bonds from the insurer.;   The transactions put highlyliquid securities on Guarantee's books and removed the illiquid junk bonds,allowing Guarantee to file documents with regulators that portrayed itsfinancial health as better than it was, officials involved in the case said.;  In a statement, Merrill confirmed that it was being investigated but said itstransactions with Guarantee Security were proper.;   &quot;Merrill Lynch stronglydenies it engaged in any illegal or unethical activity with regard tosecurities transactions that were done as far back as 1984 by GuaranteeSecurity,&quot; the firm said.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  New York Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911010  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  242  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, October 10, 199100284078,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>